remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKPathBuilder` provides a mutable builder for constructing an <xref:SkiaSharp.SKPath>
incrementally. Use the `MoveTo`, `LineTo`, `CubicTo`, `QuadTo`, `ConicTo`, and `ArcTo`
family of methods to add contours, then call <xref:SkiaSharp.SKPathBuilder.Snapshot> to
produce a read-only snapshot or <xref:SkiaSharp.SKPathBuilder.Detach> to transfer
ownership of the path and reset the builder.

This type wraps a native Skia resource and implements `IDisposable`. Always dispose of
it when done, either with a `using` statement or by calling `Dispose()` directly.

## Examples

```csharp
using var builder = new SKPathBuilder();
builder.MoveTo(0, 0);
builder.LineTo(100, 0);
builder.LineTo(100, 100);
builder.Close();

using var path = builder.Detach();
canvas.DrawPath(path, paint);
```
